In [[point-set topology]], the '''composant''' of a point ''p'' in a [[Continuum (topology)|continuum]] ''A'' is the [[Union (set theory)|union]] of all proper subcontinua of ''A'' that [[Element (mathematics)|contain]] ''p''.  If a continuum is [[Indecomposable continuum|indecomposable]], then its composants are [[pairwise disjoint]].  The composants of a continuum are [[Dense set|dense]] in that continuum.

