'''Robert Fountain''' is a [[United Kingdom|British]] [[mental calculator]]. He won the first [[Mental Calculation World Cup]] in 2004 and the second [[Mental Calculation World Cup]] in 2006.<ref>[https://www.handelsblatt.com/technik/forschung-innovation/brite-ist-bester-kopfrechner-der-welt/2427834.html Handelsblatt, 01.11.2004]</ref><ref>[http://www.focus.de/wissen/mensch/rechen-wm_aid_118643.html Focus Magazin, 04.11.2006]</ref><ref>[http://www.tagesspiegel.de/weltspiegel/robert-fountain-weltmeister-im-kopfrechnen/770670.html Der Tagesspiegel, 4/11/2006]</ref> In 1999 he was recognised by the [[Mind Sports Organisation]] as the first Grandmaster of [[Mental Calculation]]. Fountain was inspired to take up [[mental calculation]] as a hobby at the age of 11 after seeing [[Willem Klein|Wim Klein]] performing on television.<ref>[http://www.symmetrymagazine.org/article/december-2012/%E2%80%98human-calculator%E2%80%99-wim-klein-advanced-physics-inspired-others Symmetry Magazine, December 2012]</ref> He is co-author of ''The Mental Calculator's Handbook''.<ref name="Fountain and van koningsveld">{{Cite book | isbn = 978-1-300-84665-9 | last = Robert Fountain | first = Jan van Koningsveld | title = The Mental Calculator's Handbook | date = 2013 }}</ref>
